<title>PORTUGAL: BTA shares drop 11 percent.</title>
<headline>BTA shares drop 11 percent.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1997-01-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Banco Totta e Acores fell 11 percent at the opening on Lisbon bourse to 2,700 escudos after the announcement of lower than expected results and dividends and the resignation of BTA president Alipio Dias, dealers said.  </p>
<p>BTA said on Friday it expected to distribute a 1996 gross dividend of 135 escudos per share. The market had expected a 1996 dividend of 190 escudos per share, identical to 1995.</p>
<p>BTA said it expected to post 1996 net consolidated profit of 15 billion escudos, down from 17.2 billion in 1995.</p>
<p>-- Lisbon newsroom +351-1-3538254</p>
